<p style="font-size:.88rem;color:#ccc;line-height:1.6">Cheap calendered vinyl fails in 12–18 months in Chicago winters. We use only Avery Dennison MPI 1105 cast vinyl — rated 5–7 years, zero paint damage claims in 10+ years.</p></div><div style="padding:0 0 0 28px"><p style="font-family:monospace;font-size:.62rem;letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#FFD700;margin-bottom:6px">Cost Efficiency</p><p style="font-size:.88rem;color:#ccc;line-height:1.6">Wraps are IRS Section 179 advertising expenses — 100% deductible year one. A $3,750 cargo van wrap costs ~$2,700 after tax at the 28% bracket. Fleet discounts up to 15%.</p></div></div></div><h2>Truck Types We Wrap</h2><ul class="services"><li><strong>Pickup Trucks</strong> — Ford F-150/F-250/F-350, Chevy Silverado, Ram 1500/2500/3500, Toyota Tundra, GMC Sierra.</li><li><strong>Box Trucks (16–22 ft)</strong> — Isuzu NPR, Ford E-450, Hino, International. <a href="/boxtruck/" style="color:var(--gold)">Box truck wraps →</a></li><li><strong>Box Trucks (24–26 ft)</strong> — Large-format billboard wraps for maximum roadside impact.</li><li><strong>Flatbed Trucks</strong> — Side rail graphics and cab wraps for construction and hauling companies.</li><li><strong>Stake Trucks</strong> — Full and partial wraps for landscape and construction stake bodies.</li><li><strong>Specialty Trucks</strong> — Cement mixers, dump trucks, tow trucks, and utility vehicles.</li></ul><h2>Full Wraps vs. Partial Truck Wraps</h2><p class="body-text"><strong>Full truck wraps</strong> cover every visible panel for maximum impact. On a box truck, that means 200+ square feet of billboard-quality advertising space per side. Full wraps generate the most impressions and deliver the best ROI for high-visibility routes.</p><p class="body-text"><strong>Partial truck wraps</strong> cover strategic panels — sides, tailgate, rear doors — at 40–60% of full wrap cost. Partial wraps are ideal for businesses starting their fleet branding or working with