$4,500</td><td>$1,200 – $2,500</td></tr></table><p class="body-text">Fleet discounts: 5% (3–4 trucks), 10% (5–9), 15% (10+). <a href="/vehicle-wrap-cost-chicago/" style="color:var(--gold)">Full pricing guide →</a></p><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><div class="faq-item"><h3>How much do truck wraps cost in Chicago?</h3><p>Pickup truck wraps cost $2,200–$3,800. Box trucks range from $4,200–$10,000 depending on size. Partial wraps start at $1,200. Fleet discounts of 5–15% apply for 3+ trucks.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3>What types of trucks can you wrap?</h3><p>We wrap all truck types: pickup trucks, box trucks (16–26 ft), flatbed trucks, stake trucks, dump trucks, cement mixers, and specialty commercial vehicles.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3>Full wrap vs partial wrap — which is better?</h3><p>Full wraps provide maximum visual impact and advertising space. Partial wraps cover key panels at 40–60% of the cost. For commercial trucks on high-traffic routes, full wraps generate significantly more impressions and ROI.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3>How long does a truck wrap last?</h3><p>Our truck wraps use premium cast vinyl rated for 5–7 years outdoors. Combined with our 2-year installation warranty, your wrap is built for years of commercial use in Chicago weather.</p></div></div>